                           saints; incipit of Text I; incipit of Text II and its subsections (fols.
                           4r, 13ra, 21rb, 21vb, 29ra, 38rb, 47vb, 65r, 74r, 83v-84r, 88rb, 90r);
                           incipit of Text III and its subsections (fols. 92v, 96vb, 97va, 98rb,
                           99ra); incipit of Text IV and its subsections (fols. 100v, 101va, 101vb,
                           102ra, 102rb, 102va, 102vb, 103ra, 103va, 104ra, 104va, 105ra, 105va,
                           105vb, 106ra, 106rb, 106va, 106vb, 107ra); elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the quire marks. 
                           
 A few groups of lines (alternating with black lines)on the incipit
                           page of Texts I, II and III; a group of lines on the incipit page of Text
                           IV.</seg>
                     </handNote>
